==English==
===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}

# a language spoken mostly in the province of [[Friesland]], in the north of the Netherlands; West Lauwers Frisian, one of the three [[Frisian]] languages (or language varieties)
# {{context|Netherlands}} the West Frisian [[dialect]] of [[Dutch]] dialect spoken in the province of [[North Holland]], related to West Frisian language

====Usage notes====
Some linguists consider West Frisian, Saterland Frisian, and North Frisian to be varieties of a single language called “'''Frisian'''”.  Other linguists and the speakers consider them to be separate languages in a language group called “'''Frisian'''”.

